"刑事责任能力:\"刑事责任能力\" (Criminal Responsibility Capacity) refers to the legal capacity of an individual to be held accountable for their actions under the law. This concept encompasses the ability of a person to understand the nature, significance, and consequences of their actions, as well as their capacity to consciously control their behavior and take responsibility for it. In legal contexts, particularly in cases involving mental disorders, an individual's 刑事责任能力 is often assessed to determine whether they can be held legally responsible for their conduct. This dual understanding highlights both the cognitive and volitional aspects of the concept, emphasizing the importance of mental awareness and self-control in the legal evaluation of responsibility.", "受审能力:受审能力是指刑事案件的犯罪嫌疑人、被告人在刑事诉讼中，对法律赋予自己的权利、义务和刑事诉讼的意义的认识理解以及接受刑事审判的能力", "服刑能力:服刑能力是指精神疾病患者在服刑期间是否具备接受刑罚的能力", "作证能力:作证能力是指精神疾病患者在刑事诉讼中是否具备作证的能力", "民事行为能力:\"民事行为能力\" (Civil Capacity) refers to the legal ability of an individual to engage in civil activities, particularly in the context of mental health conditions. This concept is often assessed in legal settings to determine whether individuals with mental disorders, such as schizophrenia, possess the capacity to make independent judgments and manage their affairs rationally. The assessment of civil capacity takes into account the varying stages and severity of the mental disorder, categorizing individuals into three levels: full capacity, limited capacity, and no capacity. In essence, 民事行为能力 evaluates whether a person with a mental disorder can legally participate in civil activities and make decisions, with the determination based on their ability to understand and act in a reasoned manner.", "诉讼能力:诉讼能力是指精神疾病患者在参与刑事或民事诉讼时是否具备相应的法律能力", "自我防卫能力:自我防卫能力是指精神疾病患者在其人身、财产等合法权益遭受侵害时是否具备自我防卫的能力", "精神损伤:精神损伤是指精神疾病患者因外部因素导致的精神功能损害。在精神损伤的评定中，特别是在涉及精神分裂症患者的人身损害赔偿案件中，分析生活事件即心理刺激因素对疾病产生的作用至关重要。通过诱发因素的描述，可以明确生活事件与精神分裂症之间的关系，从而评估外部因素对患者精神功能的影响。这一过程不仅有助于理解精神损伤的成因，也为相关法律案件的裁决提供了科学依据。", "CIVIL CAPABILITY:Civil capability refers to a citizen's ability to acquire civil rights and undertake civil obligations through their own actions, thereby establishing, altering, or terminating legal relationships. It is the qualification for one's actions to have civil legal effect.\"", "MENTAL DAMAGE:Mental damage refers to the disorder of brain function activities caused by external physical, chemical, biological, or psychological factors, resulting in cognitive, emotional, volitional, and behavioral disturbances or deficiencies. It is the mental dysfunction that occurs after exposure to external harmful factors, including both physical brain injuries and psychological stimuli.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}